            title: "Diagnose Your Stage Before Choosing a Strategy",
            description: "Before selecting tactics, identify which stage of change you are actually in. If you are in pre-contemplation or contemplation — if you are genuinely ambivalent about whether you want to change — the most important work is motivational, not tactical. List the genuine costs and benefits of changing versus not changing. Talk to someone who has made the change you are considering. Resolve the ambivalence before committing to a system. Starting a tactical system while ambivalent produces the most common pattern in behavior change: an energetic start followed by rapid abandonment when the ambivalence reasserts itself."
